The paper deals with image stitching, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of graph-based hypothesis generation and seam-guided local alignment suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The improved efficiency and effectiveness of the proposed method also suggest the use of optimization and learning algorithms (cs.LG).
